Fall back to pread/pwrite when copy_file_range returns ENOSYS.

Some restricted runtime environments (gVisor, certain seccomp filters,
older kernels < 4.5) do not implement the copy_file_range(2) syscall and
return ENOSYS.  Without this patch zig itself aborts with
`thread N panic: TODO` while symbolising the stack trace in the
unexpectedErrno path.

Two independent copy_file_range wrappers need the fix:

  - std.posix.copy_file_range — already has a pread/pwrite fallback below
    the syscall loop, we just need to `break` on .NOSYS the same way
    it already does on .INVAL and .XDEV.

  - std.os.linux.File.copy_file_range (the thin `CopyFileRangeError`
    wrapper used by std.fs.File.Writer.sendFile) — returns
    error.OperationNotSupported so the caller's existing error path
    is exercised and the writer records `copy_file_range_err` to skip
    subsequent calls.

--- a/lib/std/posix.zig
+++ b/lib/std/posix.zig
@@ -6425,6 +6425,7 @@
                     .PERM => return error.PermissionDenied,
                     .TXTBSY => return error.SwapFile,
                     .XDEV => break, // support for cross-filesystem copy added in Linux 5.3, use fallback
+                    .NOSYS => break, // syscall unavailable (gVisor, old kernels, seccomp), use fallback
                     else => |err| return unexpectedErrno(err),
                 }
             }
--- a/lib/std/os/linux.zig
+++ b/lib/std/os/linux.zig
@@ -9819,6 +9819,7 @@
             .PERM => return error.PermissionDenied,
             .TXTBSY => return error.SwapFile,
             .XDEV => return error.NotSameFileSystem,
+            .NOSYS => return error.OperationNotSupported,
             else => |err| return unexpectedErrno(err),
         }
     }
